content: Hello. Am I mistaken or we do not have a notion of a model being saturated, right? I was looking around docs#ModelTheory.Types but did not see anything that looked like it.
Maybe let me impose on the kindness of @Aaron Anderson
We only have the most basic definitions of types, no saturation or homogeneity (outside the relevance to Fraisse theory).
Good, that was what I thought. Thank you!
Luigi Massacci has marked this topic as resolved.
